The White House Press Secretary, Robert Gibbs, held a press briefing on May 7, 2009. During the briefing, he addressed various topics, including the proposed budget cuts, the stress test results for banks, the potential for more bank bailouts, and the President's commitment to fiscal sustainability. Gibbs also discussed the need for education reform and the President's belief in bipartisan solutions. He mentioned the importance of cutting wasteful spending, closing tax loopholes, and evaluating programs that don't work. Additionally, he commented on the issue of performance-enhancing drugs in sports and expressed disappointment in the use of such substances. The briefing concluded with Gibbs stating that the President would release a picture from the Air Force One fly-by incident in Manhattan and that the President did not plan to make any political endorsements in the New York mayoral race.